However, the following months showed that Bush's strategy, which emanates from the recommendations of campaign commanders, was the only possible and likely to be successful to such an extent that the newspapers currently do not speak of Iraq at all.
This has not improved Bush's reputation, which says, objectively speaking, he left his successor a far more favourable final situation than could be expected.
Barack Obama hopes that in Afghanistan the miracle will happen again
It was again the campaign commanders who requested an increase in the military contingent, including the commander of the Afghan operation, General Stanley McCristal, who even severely criticized the reluctance of the White House despite the habits of subordination.
He asked 40,000 men to make the situation more favourable.
The president hesitated for three months but without a better option, he at least cheated the general of 10,000 soldiers.
He has succeeded in removing the promise of an additional 5,000 from Europe, even if it was originally 10,000.
What brings the most problems throughout Obama's strategy seems to be his intention to withdraw Afghanistan's armies within 18 months and to complete this whole process within three years. All of Obama's doctrine brings more questions than it provides answers.
Many doubt that an increase of half will bring the same fruit as the progress in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars of recent years, Iraqi society is relatively well organized and its leaders honour agreements.
The Afghan situation stands out by the exact opposite - no one can rely on and no treaty is respected.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, accustomed to changing leadership day by day according to what arranges them.
Political institutions, although officially founded, will only remain powder in the eyes behind which patriarchal ethnic relations will proliferate.
It is particularly complex to balance the interests of the various ethnic groups in view of the lack of clarity about the reports, which are still complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Even the foundation of a "ready state to act", which is the basic purpose of the operation, does not seem to be very real.
The temporal horizon of Obama's strategy makes his volunteerism perplexed.
Over the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has only worsened and is currently on the brink of chaos.
Only a purely romantic heart and out of reality can be convinced that the small soldiers sent into the tumult of war for their "fast return home" will bring there a real miracle.
From a political point of view, defining a date for the withdrawal of troops is purely irresponsible, since the Taliban will regard it as the indirect asset of the American defeat.
The last NATO summit showed that the Europeans' willingness to participate in military operations in Afghanistan is oriented towards the negative.
European policies do not know or want to explain to their voters how security in Germany or Italy is linked to a war in the mountains of Hindu Kush.
Another factor that can radically alter the situation is the evolution of events related to Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and strengthened sanctions have no effect on Iranians, the Americans will face the very difficult issue of solving the problem through the use of military force.
For example, it will be necessary to answer when, according to Obama, America will come to the victorious withdrawal of Afghanistan's troops.
However, each such solution will result in a dramatic reversal of the Afghan situation.
The only roust for Obama is that it remains three years until the presidential elections and therefore there is still enough time for him to plan on a new strategy, in case it would prove to be a total fiasco.
